==English==

===Noun===
'''[[ham]] and [[egg]]er

# Disdainful remark directed at someone deemed worthless or undesirable.
# (''professioanl wrestling slang'') A preliminary wrestler; a [[jobber]].

===Usage===
The term '''ham-and-egger''' was frequently used by professional wrestling personality Bobby Heenan, who disdainfully called fans - especially those who disapproved of his rulebreaking tactics - as "ham-and-eggers."